News_Snippet: Nvidia Q3 Revenue $35.1B (Beat estimates). Data Center grew 112%. HOWEVER, Q4 guidance of $37.5B, while beating consensus, missed the 'whisper numbers' ($38B+) of aggressive traders. Margins dipped slightly due to Blackwell ramp-up.
Tesla Q3 Revenue $25.18B (Missed estimates of $25.37B). BUT, EPS smashed expectations ($0.72 vs $0.58) and gross margins surged to 19.8%. Musk forecasted 20-30% volume growth for 2025.
Apple Q4 Revenue $94.9B (Beat). iPhone 16 sales grew. HOWEVER, Net Income slumped due to a one-time $10B EU tax charge. Service revenue growth missed expectations slightly.
Signal_Type: Top Line Beat but Bottom Line Hit

News_Snippet: Microsoft Q1 Revenue $65.6B (Beat). Azure grew 33%. BUT, CFO warned that Azure growth would decelerate in Q2 due to supply constraints, overshadowing the beat.
Meta Q3 Revenue $40.6B (Beat). BUT, Daily Active Users (DAU) missed slightly. Zuckerberg warned of 'significant capital expenditure growth' for AI in 2025, reigniting spending fears.
AMD Q3 Revenue beat slightly. Data Center revenue doubled. HOWEVER, Q4 revenue guidance ($7.5B) was merely in-line, failing to meet the sky-high expectations for AI chip market share capture.
Amazon Q3 Earnings crushed estimates. Operating Income $17.4B (vs $14.7B exp). AWS growth accelerated to 19%. This was a 'Clean Beat', contrasting with MSFT/META's spending warnings.
Alphabet Q3 Revenue $88.3B (Beat). Cloud revenue soared 35% to $11.4B. Operating margins expanded. A strong validation of AI investment returns.
Super Micro Computer auditor (EY) resigned, stating they could 'no longer rely on management's representations'. Stock plunged 33%. This contradicted previous management reassurances.
Dell Q3 Revenue $24.4B (Missed estimates). AI server shipments were strong ($2.9B) BUT traditional PC business lagged significantly. Guidance was also light.
ASML leaked earnings early: Bookings €2.6B (Huge Miss vs €5.6B exp). Cut 2025 guidance citing 'slow recovery' in non-AI chips. Triggered a global semi sell-off.
Shopify Q3 Revenue surged 26% (Beat). Operating income doubled. Management gave bullish holiday guidance, defying the 'weak consumer' narrative.
Palantir Q3 Revenue beat and raised full-year guidance. US Commercial revenue +54%. Cited 'insatiable' AI demand. Valuation concerns ignored by market.
Visa Q4 Revenue/EPS beat estimates. Payment volume +8%. HOWEVER, the company faces a massive DOJ antitrust lawsuit filed in Sept, creating a 'Results vs Regulation' conflict.
Lululemon Q3 Earnings beat estimates. BUT revenue growth slowed to 9% (lowest in years) and Americas growth was flat. Guidance cautious.
Disney Q4 Earnings beat. Streaming business profitable. BUT, Parks (Experiences) revenue declined 6% internationally. CFO warned of modest growth in 2025.
IBM Q3 Revenue missed estimates ($14.9B vs $15.0B) due to consulting weakness. HOWEVER, AI book of business grew to $3B. Stock fell 6%.
UnitedHealth beat Q3 earnings. BUT lowered top end of full-year guidance due to higher medical costs and coding audits. Stock dropped.
Airbnb Q3 Revenue beat slightly. BUT Q4 guidance was soft, warning of shorter booking windows and weaker US demand.
JPMorgan Q3 Profit beat estimates. Net Interest Income surprised to the upside. Jamie Dimon warned of geopolitical risks, but consumer remains 'healthy'.
Goldman Sachs Q3 Profit surged 45% on strong investment banking fees. Trading revenue also beat. Signals a rebound in M&A activity.
Bank of America Q3 Earnings beat estimates. Trading revenue rose 12%. Investment banking fees rose 18%. Warren Buffett has been selling the stock, creating a 'Results vs Guru Action' conflict.
(Market Reaction) Following ASML's miss, Nvidia and AMD stocks fell 4-5% in sympathy, creating a 'Guilt by Association' buying opportunity as their fundamentals remained strong.
Cisco Q1 Earnings beat. Revenue dropped 6% YoY but less than feared. AI orders exceeded $300M. Raised full-year guidance.
Salesforce Q3 Earnings beat ($2.41 vs $2.26). Revenue beat. BUT Q4 revenue guidance was light. Agentforce AI platform is launching but monetization is early stage.
Walmart Q3 Earnings beat. Raised full-year outlook. US comparable sales +5.3%. E-commerce +27%. Signals strong consumer spending despite inflation.
Target Q3 Earnings missed significantly (EPS $1.85 vs $2.30). Cut full-year guidance. Cited supply chain costs and weak discretionary spending. Stock crashed 20%.
Netflix Q3 Earnings beat. Subscriber adds +5M (Beat). Margins expanded. Said they will stop reporting subscriber numbers in 2025, creating long-term opacity fears.
UPS Q3 Revenue beat estimates for first time in 2 years. Profit rose. Signals freight recession might be bottoming. FedEx had missed earlier.
Nike Q1 Earnings beat estimates but Revenue missed. Withdrew full-year guidance ahead of CEO transition. Stock fell.
Oracle Q2 Earnings missed revenue estimates slightly. Cloud growth +25% (strong but slowing). Stock fell 8% despite partnership announcements.
CrowdStrike Q3 Earnings beat. Raised guidance. Revenue +29%. Confirmed full recovery from July IT outage. Stock rose.
Micron Q1 Earnings beat. Forecasted strong Q2 revenue driven by AI memory (HBM) demand. Stock rose.
Boeing Q3 reported $6B loss. Workers rejected contract offer (strike continued). CEO Ortberg outlined 'fundamental culture change' needed.
(Late Reaction) Intel ejected from Dow Jones Industrial Average, replaced by Nvidia. Marks symbolic end of an era. Stock sentiment hit all-time low.
US Oct Non-Farm Payrolls +12k (Huge Miss vs 100k+ exp). Unemployment 4.1%. BLS cited hurricanes and Boeing strike as distortions. Market ignored the miss.
US Nov Non-Farm Payrolls +227k (Beat). Unemployment 4.2%. Confirmed Oct was a fluke. Wages grew 4.0% YoY.
US Oct CPI 2.6% YoY (Met expectations). Core CPI 3.3%. Inflation progress stalled. Traders trimmed bets on aggressive 2025 cuts.
US Nov CPI 2.7% YoY. Core CPI 3.3%. Inflation remains stubborn. Fed expected to cut in Dec but signal 'skip' for Jan.
Fed cuts rates by 25bps to 4.50-4.75%. Powell says election result has 'no effect' on near-term decisions. Language on inflation confidence slightly softened.
US Q3 GDP Advance Estimate +2.8% (Missed 3.0%). Consumer spending +3.7% (Strong). Core PCE inflation 2.2%. 'Soft Landing' narrative intact.
Donald Trump wins US Presidency. S&P 500 futures surged. 'Trump Trade' (Banks, Crypto, Small Caps) rallied. Renewables fell.
US Oct PPI rose 0.2% (Met exp). But services inflation showed stickiness. Bond yields rose as market feared Fed might pause cuts.
(Released Oct) Sept Jobs +254k (Huge Beat). Unemployment fell to 4.1%. Crushed recession fears. Yields surged as market priced out 50bps cuts.
US Oct Retail Sales +0.4% (Beat). Control group weaker. Suggests consumer is selective but not breaking.
(Released Oct) Sept CPI 2.4% (Hotter than 2.3% exp). Core 3.3%. 'Last mile' of inflation proving difficult.
Fed Minutes from Nov meeting showed officials favored gradual cuts but were open to pausing if inflation stalled. 'Gradualism' emphasized.
(Hypothetical based on trend) Fed official Waller signals 'skip' for January meeting citing sticky CPI. Market odds for Jan cut drop.
ISM Manufacturing PMI 47.2 (Contracting). Employment component weak. Fed 'policy error' fears briefly resurfaced.
Cyber Monday / Black Friday sales hit record $13.3B (+7%). Mobile shopping dominated. Adobe Analytics data confirmed consumer spending power.
